## Drupal Conventions

### How to Work
- When asked to plan: output only the plan. No code until told to proceed
- When given a plan: follow it exactly. Flag real problems and wait
- State assumptions before coding. If uncertain or multiple interpretations exist, present them - don't pick silently
- Transform tasks into verifiable goals. "Add validation" -> "Write test for invalid input, then make it pass"
- Re-read any file before editing it. After editing, re-read it. Edit tool fails silently on stale matches
- On any rename or signature change: grep for direct calls, type references, imports, re-exports, test mocks. Assume grep missed something
- Every changed line must trace to the task. No unrequested improvements, no adjacent cleanup
- If you notice unrelated issues, mention them - don't fix them
- Never attempt multi-file changes in one response. Max 5 files, then verify
- When I say "yes" or "do it": execute. Don't repeat the plan
- When corrected: don't repeat the mistake. If a pattern keeps failing, stop and state where your mental model is wrong
- Match existing codebase style. My working code is a better spec than my description
- If a simpler approach exists, say so. Push back when warranted
- Remove imports/functions YOUR changes made unused. Don't remove pre-existing dead code
- Never delete a file without verifying nothing references it
- Work from raw error data. Don't guess. If a bug report has no output, ask for it

### Drupal-Specific Rules
- Services and DI via `*.services.yml`. Never `\Drupal::service()` in service classes
- `\Drupal::` static calls only in `.module` files and procedural hooks
- Entity API for data access, not direct DB queries
- Config via `config/sync/` - never modify config directly in database. Run `drush cex` after changes
- Never modify contrib modules. Use hooks, events, or Composer patches
- Check theme before writing frontend: know the base theme and CSS framework
- Render arrays must include `#cache` with tags, contexts, and max-age

### Workflow
```
/discover [description]    # Scope task, detect stack
/blueprint {issue-name}    # Implementation plan
/implement {issue-name}    # Build phase by phase
/review {issue-name}       # Code review
/retro {issue-name}        # Lessons learned
/status                    # Check incomplete workflows
```
Quick tasks (bug fixes, config changes) skip the workflow - just fix, validate, commit.

### Team Practices
- One developer per task. Don't have two people working on the same module - AI merge conflicts are painful
- Create a PR after `/retro` completes. Every task should be a pull request
- Personal preferences go in `CLAUDE.local.md` (not committed). Team standards stay in `CLAUDE.md`

### Hooks (Recommended)
Set up in `.claude/settings.local.json` (not committed) to catch errors during implementation:
```json
{
  "hooks": {
    "PostToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Edit|Write",
        "command": "php -l $CLAUDE_FILE_PATH 2>&1 | head -5"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

### Git
- `.claude/planning/` - gitignore if internal only
- Branch: `feature/{issue-name}`, `fix/{issue-name}`
- Always `drush cex` and commit `config/sync/` after config changes

